722607f-a.text:
Pinehurst Ave., south from West 183rd Street (left) and showing on the west side of same, a portion of the apartment house development, known as the Hudson View Gardens. The immediate foreground was the
former site of Fort Washington.
November 17, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

722609f-a.text:
Pinehurst Ave., north from West 183rd (right) Street. Shown on the left are portions of a major real estate development by Dr. Charles V. Paterno and called the Hudson View Gardens. Fort Washington, of Revolutionary War fane stood in the foreground, slightly north of the present 183rd Street; Pinehurst Ave. would divide its western wing into
equal parts.
November 18, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

722610f-a.text:
Pinehurst Ave., south from West 183rd (left) Street. Shown on the right are portions of the Hudson View Gardens; the buildings on the left,
at the S.E. corner of West 181st Street.
November 18, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
